This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with generating face images from speech. It also involves learning disentangled audio-visual representation, which could fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper mentions the tasks of automatic lip reading and audio-video retrieval, which could be related to natural language processing (cs.CL) and signal processing (cs.SD).
